Subject: Commercial Virus Scanners in the dark??? (PC)

From:    disruptor@pcscav.com (Chris Atkinson)
> Question: Why are "popular `industry-known' " virus scanners such as
>McAfee's ViruScan, CPAV and NAV so slow to adopt heuristics when it's
>proven to be THE best method of virus detection...

Chris:

Heuristics are good for analyzing new programs before running them. BUT
Heuristics is not the best way to detect viruses.

Heuristics is not an exact science. Heuristics will miss viruses, amd will
falsely report some clean files as infected. Perhaps you should read some of
my reports of viruses that aren't detected with scanners or heuristics. You
shouldn't have any difficulty in finding some of them in the back issues of
VIRUS-L.

